# Aretide core standards

**Company:** Aretide ([aretide.com](https://aretide.com/)) — HIPAA-aligned telehealth weight-loss intake.

**Mindset:** Senior SWE + QA. Nothing is a prototype. Ship production-quality code, validation, and tests on every change.

**After code changes:** run `npm run test:all` (includes backend `smoke_clinical_flow` integration smoke). Fix failures; explain them in chat. Add tests when behavior is new or uncovered.

**Lint:** ESLint on **changed** `.ts`/`.tsx` files only (`npx eslint <paths>` or git-diff pipe). Do **not** run `npm run lint` on the whole repo.

**TypeScript:** run `npx tsc --noEmit` whenever you change TS/TSX — **required**, not optional. ESLint does not catch missing imports in route files; Vitest does not typecheck `src/routes/`.

**New user input (frontend or backend):**
1. Validators in frontend (`src/lib/form-validation.ts`, step files) AND backend (`backend/apps/common/validation/` + serializer)
2. Tests with SQL injection, XSS, path traversal, command injection, overflow — see `docs/INPUT_VALIDATION_TESTS.md`
3. Backend API test returning 400 on malicious payloads

**PHI:** never in localStorage/sessionStorage. Parameterized DB queries only. See **`docs/HIPAA.md`** for full compliance checklist.

**Colors / portal UI:** raw palette in `src/styles.css`; usage in **`src/lib/design-tokens.ts`**. Use `AccountSectionCard` + `SectionTone` — see **`AGENTS.md` § Design system & color scheme**. Never ad hoc colors.

**Agent docs:** read `AGENTS.md` first. If agent docs disagree with the codebase, propose the fix to the user — do not edit `AGENTS.md` or rules without approval.

**Authoritative docs:** `AGENTS.md`, `docs/INPUT_VALIDATION_TESTS.md`, `backend/DATABASE.md`
